children.subject:
ive taken that schedule and had also taken 70/hug 61b the previous semester and i felt the 61c/16a combo was significantly more work.

eecs 16a has a huge chunk for lab and more notes than 70 + self-grades and everything so even though the material is easier, the time commitment is much more.

Same with 61b and 61c. I would say Hug 61b projects are comparable to the level of a 61c lab, so the workload of 61c was easily 3x for me in 61c from 61b. I think it depends on the person and their prior experience but I'd probably study up on 61c before a bit and be prepared for a tougher schedule.
